<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881108-0051 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Noted... </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TL WNEWS KPE WPPGY </CO><TEXT>   MAGAZINE: Time Inc. agreed to publish an Italian edition of Fortune magazine in a venture with Italian publisher Arnoldo Mondadori Editore early next year. Initial circulation is expected to be 50,000.    WHO'S NEWS: Patrick M. Williamson will step down as president and chief executive officer of Columbia Pictures Entertainment Inc.'s Triumph Releasing Corp., effective Jan. 1. He will become a consultant to Columbia, a New York-based entertainment company. J. Edward Shugrue, senior executive vice president of Triumph, will take the posts on that date. . . . Patricia D. Yoder, senior vice president at PNC Financial Corp., has been named executive vice president and Southeast region general manager of Hill andamp; Knowlton USA, the international public relations arm of WPP Group PLC, effective Jan. 3. </TEXT></DOC>